 century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."]}]},{"name":"Ap","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Gwilim Ap Einion was born about 1480, in Cardiff, Glamorgan, Wales as the son of Einion ap Elffin. He married Mrs. Einon in 1499, in Cardiff, Glamorgan, Wales. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 3 daughters."},"et":{"about 1480–":"umbes 1480–Surnud","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1485–Female":"1485–Surnud","1500–1523":"1500–1523","1529–Female":"1529–Surnud","1530–Male":"1530–Surnud","1532–Male":"1532–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1460–Male":"1460–Surnud","about 1480":"umbes 1480","1523":"1523","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1485":"1485","1460":"1460","1529":"1529","1480":"1480","Cardiff, Glamorgan, Wales":"Cardiff, Glamorgan, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Llwyn-Dafydd, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Llwyn-Dafydd, Cardiganshire, Wales","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1480–":"noin 1480–Kuollut","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","1485–Female":"1485–Kuollut","1500–1523":"1500–1523","1529–Female":"1529–Kuollut","1530–Male":"1530–Kuollut","1532–Male":"1532–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1460–Male":"1460–Kuollut","about 1480":"noin 1480","1523":"1523","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1532":"1532","1530":"1530","1485":"1485","1460":"1460","1529":"1529","1480":"1480","Cardiff, Glamorgan, Wales":"Cardiff, Glamorgan, Wales","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Llwyn-Dafydd, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Llwyn-Dafydd, Cardiganshire, Wales","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1480–":"environ 1480–Décédé","1480–Male":"1480–Décédé","1485–Female":"1485–Décédée","1500–